The detailed study of an already existing thermoelectric refrigeration system with a capacity of 5 to 45 l, voltage requirements varying from 100 to 120 V, functional properties, and design consideration from the previous mechanical test data was used to create an optimized CAD model of thermoelectric refrigeration box, using the NXCAD 10.0 software. There are three models: (a) TER model with sharp edges, (b) TER model with partially round edges, and (c) TER model with fully round edges [36]. The analysis for the designs was conducted considering thermal flux, streamlines, and velocity as the main factors. These factors affect the expected outcomes of computational fluid dynamics. The simulation model is prepared by analysing material and design to check the manufacturing complexities for thermoelectric refrigeration as mentioned in Fig. 1. Data obtained by simulation of the thermoelectric refrigerator were used to calculate the performance of the selected module for comparison. The overall types of warmth retention and warmth dismissal are introduced in Eqs. (1) and (2). The results are plotted in the graphs for comparing the various parameters of the refrigerator [37].1Qc=αITc-0.5I2R-Kt(Th-Tc)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
